-- German Companies Fear Collapse of Euro, Die Welt Survey of 700 Firms Shows
-- Jeremy van Loon
-- 2010-06-28T06:00:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-28/german-companies-fear-collapse-of-euro-die-welt-survey-of-700-firms-shows.html

          
          
             Almost half of German companies
surveyed by Ernst & Young LLP fear a collapse of the euro,  Die
Welt  reported.  
 Of the 700 companies questioned, 47 percent said the
currency might break down according to a June survey, compared
with 34 percent in February, the newspaper reported.  
